FileSurf-Help
=============

CD [directory]                Changes the working-directory to the given path.
or CHDIR                      If no parameter is given, you are told about
                              the current working directory.

XDIR                          Shows the files of the current path. Also CALL and
                              a short discription of the files is shown.

DIR [options] [directory]     Shows the files of the given path. If no
                              parameter is given, the files of the current
                              directory are listed.
                              Possible options:
                              -D: sort by file-modification-time
                              -S: sort by file-size
                              -N: do not sort (this means the files will be
                                  listed in order of their creation)

LS [options] [directory]      Does the same as DIR does, except that the
                              directory-content is given in short format.
                              By stating the -L option, the long format is
                              used anyway

PATH                          Lists the directories, from which users may
                              read and to which users may write.

NEW <name>                    Lists all new files. Reduce output with "name"
                              search string.

FIND <name>                   Searches "name" in all filesurf filenames.

INFO <file>                   Shows some information above file.

VIEW <file>                   Lists the file-archiv.

GET <file>                    Sends the given file in plain-text mode.
or READ
or TYPE                       !!! You cannot read a binary file !!!
or CAT                        !!!      using this command       !!!
or RTEXT

7GET <file>                   Sends the given file in 7Plus mode.

7MAIL <file> <parts>          Sends the given File as 7Plus message into
                              mailbox.

BGET <file>                   Sends the given file in AutoBIN mode.
or BIN
or RPRG

BMAIL <file>                  Sends the given file as AutoBIN message into 
                              user board.
                              
BSGET <file> <parts>          Sends the given file in binary parts.

DGET <file>                   Sends the given file in DIDADIT mode.

YGET <file>                   Sends the given file in YAPP mode.
or RYAPP

PUT <file>                    Saves the given file in plain-text mode.
or WTEXT

BPUT <file>                   Saves the given file in AutoBIN mode.
or WPRG

DPUT                          Save a file in DIDADIT mode.

YPUT <file>                   Saves the given file in YAPP mode.
or WYAPP

HELP                          Sends this text.
or ?

QUIT                          Terminates the FileSurf mode and returns
or BYE                        to the mailbox prompt.
or EXIT
